ExperienceSummary.Description: The candidate is experienced in:  User Experience (User Research); and Information Technology. The candidate has 5 years of work experience.

Positions.Description:
Using Figma, designed and created an interactive website prototype from concept to preliminary
testing for Self Esteem Brands' subsidiary companies, Anytime Fitness and Healthy Contributions.
• Worked closely with a team of 10 developers and product designers to implement content and design
changes.

• Website design included an easy to use selection for employee wellness packages that will be seen by
an average of 80 corporate partners per month.
• Proposed user testing methodology for the team to continue forward with next stages in development.

55446	•  Presented data collected during research to give a conclusion on how efficiency was changed in the
2011 - 2015	update and to what degree users were unsatisfied with the changes.
Relevant Coursework
RESEARCH METHODS IN HUMAN-COMPUTER INTERACTION
Survey, discussion, and application of historical and recent research in the field of human-computer
interaction with an emphasis on visual presentation, analysis, and communication of data and information; research methods, techniques, current readings, and best practices.
HUMAN-COMPUTER INTERACTION
The basic theories, principles and guidelines of the design and evaluation of human-computer
interactions. Employed participatory design, low and high-fidelity prototyping, user interface technologies, and quantitative and qualitative evaluation of user interfaces.

Responsible for reading and setting planograms, resetting aisles and endcaps, and creating product
displays for seasonal events.

•  Provided creative and logistic input into sets when needed to provide best product displays.
•  Developed skills in teamwork, collaboration, adaptive learning, design, communication, and multitasking.
College Project Experience

INFORMATION VISUALIZATION	| INFORMATICS CAPSTONE
•  Blended 8,000+ entry datasets and created effective, interactive data visualizations in a Tableau
Dashboard to accomplish user tasks.
•  Performed user testing of graphical user interfaces with 8 student participants using Human-Computer
Interaction (HCI) testing methods, providing insight into necessary interface changes for better
usability.
•  Improved Tableau Dashboard layout and design based on user input providing improved task
effectiveness timing by around 10 seconds on average.

ALCONOMIC	| ALCOHOL SPENDING APPLICATION
•  Utilized Personas, user experience, and usability principles to create a user-friendly application to log
money spent and blood alcohol content estimate.
•  Developed an interactive, high-fidelity prototype with HTML5 and CSS3 through GitHub collaboration
ensuring efficient teamwork.

•  Analyzed user feedback from over 50 drinking-age students by conducting usability testing, providing
Bachelor's Degree in Informatics: valuable recommendations for prototype changes and giving insight into future software
Human-Computer Interaction	 implementations.
